## Usage

```bash
# Authenticate with GCP first
gcloud auth application-default login

# ── Environment variables (optional shortcut) ──────────────────────────────────
export GVM_PROJECT=my-project
export GVM_ZONE=us-central1-a
export GVM_INSTANCE=my-vm

# ── Or pass flags every time ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Get VM status
gvm --project my-project --zone us-central1-a --instance my-vm status

# Start the VM
gvm status          # (using env vars)
gvm start

# SSH with default user (ubuntu)
gvm ssh

# SSH with a custom user and key
gvm ssh --user admin --key ~/.ssh/id_rsa

# SSH with port forwarding (extra args after --)
gvm ssh -- -L 5432:localhost:5432
```

---

## How it works

| Layer | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `config.rs` | Holds `VmConfig` and builds the Compute Engine REST URL |
| `gcp.rs` | Authenticates via **Application Default Credentials** (`gcp_auth`), calls the Compute Engine v1 REST API, deserialises responses |
| `ssh.rs` | Fetches the external NAT IP via `gcp.rs`, then **replaces the process** with `ssh` on Unix (`exec`) for a native terminal experience |
| `main.rs` | Parses CLI args with `clap`, wires subcommands to the above modules |
